ecg_signal = (df['ecg'].to_numpy())
ecg_time = (df['timestamps_ecg'].to_numpy()-df['timestamps_ecg'][0])/10000

ir_signal = (df['ppg_1_ir'].dropna().to_numpy()*-1)
ir_time = (df['timestamps_ppg_1_ir'].dropna().to_numpy()-df['timestamps_ppg_1_ir'][0])/10000


## Resample
fs = 200
T_ecg = ecg_time[-1]
T_ppg = ir_time[-1]
n_ecg = int(fs*T_ecg)
n_ppg = int(fs*T_ppg)

resampled_ecg = signal.resample(ecg_signal, n_ecg, ecg_time)[0]
resampled_ppg = signal.resample(ir_signal, n_ppg, ir_time)[0]
In [ ]:
def butter_bandpass_filter(lowcut, highcut, fs, order, data):
  sampling_rate = 0.5*fs
  b,a = signal.butter(order, [lowcut/sampling_rate, highcut/sampling_rate], btype = 'band')
  y = signal.lfilter(b,a,data)
  return y

# low and high cut a bit wider range than seen in the PSD's
filtered_ecg = butter_bandpass_filter(highcut = 40, lowcut = 0.5, fs=fs, order = 2, data = resampled_ecg)
filtered_ppg = butter_bandpass_filter(highcut = 15, lowcut = 0.5, fs=fs, order = 2, data = resampled_ppg)

def slicing(sig, file_label, segment_length):

    sig_sliced = []
    label = []

    for i in np.arange(int(len(sig)/segment_length)):
        sig_sliced.append(sig[i*segment_length:(i+1)*segment_length])
        label.append(file_label)

    return (sig_sliced, label)

ecg_sliced, ecg_label = slicing(filtered_ecg, "ecg", segment_length=10*fs)
ppg_sliced, ppg_label = slicing(filtered_ppg, "ppg", segment_length=10*fs)
print(np.shape(ecg_sliced))
print(ecg_label)
print(np.shape(ppg_sliced))
print(ppg_label)

2 - Ensemble averaged waveform¶

In [ ]:
def normalize(sig):
    sig = sig - np.min(sig)
    sig = sig/np.max(sig)
    return sig
In [ ]:
def ensemble_average(signal_segments, name):

    average = np.zeros((2000))

    for segment in signal_segments:
        segment = normalize(segment)
        peaks_indices = find_peaks(segment, height = 0.65)[0]
        first_peak = peaks_indices[0]
        plt.plot(segment[first_peak:])
        average = [x+y for x, y in zip(average, np.concatenate((np.array(segment[first_peak:]),np.zeros(first_peak))))]

    plt.title(name + " all segments together")
    plt.xlabel("Time")
    plt.show()
    plt.close()
    plt.plot(np.array(average)/ len(signal_segments))
    plt.title(name + " ensemble averaged waveform")
    plt.xlabel("Time")
    plt.show()
    return average

ecg_average = ensemble_average(ecg_sliced, "ecg")
ppg_average = ensemble_average(ppg_sliced, "ppg")

Observations¶

ECG has too much variation in heart rate compared to the width of the signal, therefore the averaging smoothens the R peaks. This is not a problem with PPG, because its peaks are wider.¶

T-wave of ECG is visible only in the first 3 pulses of the ensemble averaged waveform. The diastolic peak from PPG can be seen by eye, but it is hard to extract.¶

If we only choose 2s segments, these characteristics could be collected more easily:¶
